# Authorization Policies

## Never Inline Role Checks

```typescript
// BAD
if (user.role === "ADMIN") { /* allow */ }

// GOOD
if (!AssetPolicy.canAllocate(user, asset)) {
  throw new AuthorizationError("AUTH_007");
}
```

## Rules

- One policy file per domain module: `AssetPolicy`, `BookingPolicy`, `AllocationPolicy`, `DepartmentPolicy`
- Policies are pure functions or small classes with `canView`, `canCreate`, `canApprove`, etc.
- Policies check role AND department scope where applicable
- Called from Server Actions **before** Application Service — never inside repositories
- Authorization does not belong in services or repositories

## Evaluation Chain

```
Session → Policy → Application Service → Repository
```

Identity always comes from `requireSession()` — never from request body.

## Department Head Scope

```typescript
// BAD — any department
if (user.role === "DEPARTMENT_HEAD") return true;

// GOOD — own department only
if (user.role === "DEPARTMENT_HEAD" && resource.departmentId !== user.departmentId) {
  throw new AuthorizationError("AUTH_007");
}
```
